        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4023886415" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7595853723913024125">I&apos;ve not read this author before, but was enticed to listen to this one based on a GR friend enjoying it, even though she and I don&apos;t typically read &quot;thrillers&quot;. She was right in her description of this as not so much a thriller as a complex shell game intrigue. It meanders more than gallops, but that suited my mood just fine.<br/><br/>A story that gives you interesting characters, a well-written plot, and food for thought as a murder is unwrapped within the smarmy soup of politics, pharmaceutical greed, </span>
  <span id="freeText7595853723913024125" style="display:none">I've not read this author before, but was enticed to listen to this one based on a GR friend enjoying it, even though she and I don't typically read "thrillers". She was right in her description of this as not so much a thriller as a complex shell game intrigue. It meanders more than gallops, but that suited my mood just fine.<br /><br />A story that gives you interesting characters, a well-written plot, and food for thought as a murder is unwrapped within the smarmy soup of politics, pharmaceutical greed, and rich countries preying upon those less fortunate. As I listened, I couldn't help but think of today's world pandemic; the rush to vaccinate, the unknown outcomes yet to be seen, the uneven distributions between countries, and the enormous lack of trust casting a pall over it all. <br /><br />A decent listen, if a bit long. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7595853723913024125" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


